    <item>
      <title>Re: Warrior basic questions:</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=16696#M16696</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;learn how not  to  tank&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;learn how to  balance push &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;learn the mobs  hitboxes  to  stay  at  max  weapon range&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;aquire the non  aggro  high  dps items  or  utility items you will use when not tanking&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;work with higher aggro folks and tell them  you are testing the waters on  how to get  aggro using taunt +incite line (non aggro  weapons to get  aggro after  mobs are debuffed ,  then  test  with  aggro  weapon configurations . learn how to use taunt  to get  top  aggro +maintainable aggro .&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;once  you  have these concepts working , learn  to  tank&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;learn  how and when  to  drop  aggro .&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;buff order&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;positioning&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;mob hitbox  and mob  type(rampage  flurry enrage , effects  scripts)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;start  testing  disciplines and tanking  ,  learn  mob  types, , which  use defensive ,  which  evasive , which  to  stonewall and when  to  stonewall .&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;learn  the value of sit  to  affect  positioning  .&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;experience is the best teacher , if you can't get  experience tanking  , ask somoene to  teach  you . most  warriors in  mid tier guilds  will be happy to teach  you  what they have learned , i'm  on  cazic  server  and can  be found sunday  afternoons and monday  nights eastern  times  if you have more  questions . i  no longer  am in  a top  tier  guild but  would answer  your questions if asked .&lt;/p&gt;</description>
